The article is a statement by the President of the United States on the occasion of India Republic Day. The President sends warm greetings to the people of India and people of Indian origin in America and around the world. He highlights the shared belief in democracy, liberty, pluralism, and religious tolerance between the two nations. The President emphasizes the broad and vibrant partnerships between the US and India in various fields, including science, medicine, engineering, entrepreneurship, education, and government cooperation. He mentions the shared values that form the foundation of their strong relationship and the ability to face any challenge, particularly from those who use violence to undermine free societies. The President also wishes Prime Minister Singh a quick recovery.